I01.notes:
This table is based on place of usual residence unless otherwise stated.
Same Statistical Area Level 2 (SA2); Different SA2 in: - Data are based on place of enumeration.
educational institution - Comprises 'Pre-school', 'Infants/Primary' (including Government, Catholic, Other Non Government), 'Secondary' (including Government, Catholic, Other Non Government),
'Technical or Further Educational Institution (including TAFE Colleges)', and 'University or other Tertiary Institutions'.
Highest year of school completed - Applicabale to persons aged 15 years and over.
Type of usual residence - Applicable only to persons counted at their usual residence on Census Night.
Improvised home, tent, sleepers out - Includes persons enumerated in sheds, tents, humpies, and other improvised dwellings. It also includes persons sleeping on park benches or in other rough accommodation.
Other private dwelling - Includes 'Semi-detached, row or terrace house, townhouse etc.', 'Flat, unit or apartment', 'Caravan, cabin, houseboat' and 'House or flat attached to a shop, office, etc.'.

I04.notes:
Proportion of dwellings that need 1 or more extra bedrooms is applicable to occupied private dwellings, excluding 'Visitors only' and 'Other non-classifiable' households. It is a
comparison of the number of bedrooms in a dwelling with a series of household demographics, such as the number of usual residents, their relationship to each other, age and sex.
It is based on the Canadian National Occupancy Standard. See the explanatory notes for more detail.

Partial income stated - Comprises households where at least one, but not all, members aged 15 years and over did not state an income, and/or was temporarily absent on Census Night.

I14.notes:
This table is based on place of usual residence.
In the labour force; Industry sector; Non-school qualifications - Applicable to persons aged 15 years and over.
% Unemployment - The number of unemployed persons expressed as a percentage of the total labour force.
% Labour force participation - The number of persons in the labour force expressed as a percentage of persons aged 15 years and over.
% Employment to population - The number of employed persons expressed as a percentage of persons aged 15 years and over.
CDEP participants - Community Development Employment Projects (CDEP) participants are counted as employed persons. CDEP participation is only identified on the Interviewer Household Form. These forms are designed
specifically for use in discrete Indigenous communities. Applicable to persons aged 15 years and over.
Self employed - Comprises owner managers of unincorporated enterprises with nil employees. Applicable to persons aged 15 years and over.
Same address 1 year ago; Different address 1 year ago - Excludes persons less than 1 year of age.
Same address 5 years ago; Different address 5 years ago - Excludes persons less than 5 years of age.

I16.notes:
This table is based on place of usual residence.
Worked full-time; Worked full-time; Worked full-time - 'Employed, worked full-time' is defined as having worked 35 hours or more in all jobs during the week prior to Census Night.
Away from work; Away from work; Away from work - Comprises employed persons who did not work any hours in the week prior to Census Night or who did not state their number of hours worked.
